Cameroon to Open State Banks for Agriculture, Small Companies

-- B y   P i u s   L u k o n g
-- 
2011-06-02T14:23:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-02/cameroon-to-open-state-banks-for-agriculture-small-companies.html
Cameroon will open new banks to
finance agriculture projects and support small companies,
Finance Minister Essimi Menye said.  Cameroon Rural Financial Corp. and Banque Camerounaise des
PME will each receive start-up capital of 10 billion  CFA francs 
($22 million), Menye told reporters today in Yaounde, the
capital.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Pius Lukong in Yaounde at 
 plukong@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
